Multiple explosions have just been heard in Kyiv, where air raid sirens are currently blaring throughout the capital. Unconfirmed reports indicate between three and five large blasts in the vicinity of the Ukrainian capital. The air raid sirens were heard on news channels. As the sirens and explosions sounded in Kyiv, local Pryamyy TV interrupted programming with the message: "We will be back after the air raid warning is over." See the screenshot below. Explosions have also reportedly been heard in Donetsk, the breakaway region in eastern Ukrainian.